  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishing sustainable beekeeping, income generation for subsistence small farmers and voc-COP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Burundi, beekeeping has been carried out across many generations. It plays a critical role in the livelihoods of the rural communities in five native dynamics; income generating activity; medicinal value of honey and other hive products is invaluable; supports agricultural activities through facilitating critical processes for instance cross pollination and improves crop yield; contributes immensely to forests conservation efforts and facilitates healthy linkages between biodiversity (insects and plants) towards sustainable livelihoods.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing productivity and improving quality of Honey and associated products,
Advocating for and growing the beekeeping sector 
Growing, refining and developing the honey market  		
Creating job opportunities for youth, Women and disadvantaged groups</narrative>
  </description>
